cpqn52nnVT100ScreenRefresh.name: cpqn52nnVT100ScreenRefresh
cpqn52nnVT100ScreenRefresh.description: DURABLE: This object will determine the rate, in seconds, at which the VT100 screen will refresh the automatic fields (e.g., statistics). The default value will be 5 seconds.

cpqn52nnBooterWriteCycles.name: cpqn52nnBooterWriteCycles
cpqn52nnBooterWriteCycles.description: This object will allow the user to see the number of erase/writes that have been made to the Booter firmware sectors on the FLASH PROM chip.

cpqn52nnRuntimeWriteCycles.name: cpqn52nnRuntimeWriteCycles
cpqn52nnRuntimeWriteCycles.description: This object will allow the user to see the number of erase/writes that have been made to the Runtime firmware sectors on the FLASH PROM chip.

cpqn52nnSwitchModeType.name: cpqn52nnSwitchModeType
cpqn52nnSwitchModeType.description: DURABLE: This object will determine the operational mode of the switch. The default will be store-and-forward(1). Fragment-free is not supported on 5226 nor 5226A.

cpqn52nnCreateTimeout.name: cpqn52nnCreateTimeout
cpqn52nnCreateTimeout.description: DURABLE: The minimum number of 5 minute intervals a table entry can have a status of underCreate before the agent may delete the object. The default value will be 1 5 minute interval.

cpqn52nnPowerSupplyTable.name: cpqn52nnPowerSupplyTable
cpqn52nnPowerSupplyTable.description: A table of system power supply specific information.

cpqn52nnPowerSupplyEntry.name: cpqn52nnPowerSupplyEntry
cpqn52nnPowerSupplyEntry.description: A list of information for every power supply installed

cpqn52nnPsIndex.name: cpqn52nnPsIndex
cpqn52nnPsIndex.description: A unique value for each power supply.

cpqn52nnPsStatus.name: cpqn52nnPsStatus
cpqn52nnPsStatus.description: The status of the power supply. The value good(1) is returned if the power supply identified by cpqn52nnPSIndex is running properly. The value bad(2) is returned if the power supply identified by cpqn52nnPSIndex has failed to operate properly but has been inserted into the slot. This will include an inserted power supply with no power. The value na(3) is returned if the power supply has not been inserted into the slot.

cpqn52nnHashTableSize.name: cpqn52nnHashTableSize
cpqn52nnHashTableSize.description: DURABLE: The number of address table entries, in 1024 increments, allowed for the switch. NOTE that a smaller size table will increase the likelihood of broadcasts based on unknown unicasts i.e. addresses that have not been learned. The 5226 and 5226A allows set of 8K only.

cpqn52nnMaxMemory.name: cpqn52nnMaxMemory
cpqn52nnMaxMemory.description: Kbytes of memory that can be used for RMON. Actually this number does not include some overhead needed to support the software. This number should be set in the implementation of the agent to assure that memory is always available for the overhead.

cpqn52nnMemAllocFailure.name: cpqn52nnMemAllocFailure
cpqn52nnMemAllocFailure.description: The time of the last memory allocation failure that resulted from no more physical memory available in the agent. This value is in seconds

cpqn52nnRmonMemoryCeiling.name: cpqn52nnRmonMemoryCeiling
cpqn52nnRmonMemoryCeiling.description: DURABLE: Kbytes of memory RMON code may use, not counting any overhead.

cpqn52nnStatisticsMemoryCeiling.name: cpqn52nnStatisticsMemoryCeiling
cpqn52nnStatisticsMemoryCeiling.description: DURABLE: Kbytes of memory that the RMON statistics group may use.

cpqn52nnHistoryMemoryCeiling.name: cpqn52nnHistoryMemoryCeiling
cpqn52nnHistoryMemoryCeiling.description: DURABLE: Kbytes of memory that the RMON history group may use.

cpqn52nnAlarmMemoryCeiling.name: cpqn52nnAlarmMemoryCeiling
cpqn52nnAlarmMemoryCeiling.description: DURABLE: Kbytes of memory that the RMON alarm group may use.

cpqn52nnEventMemoryCeiling.name: cpqn52nnEventMemoryCeiling
cpqn52nnEventMemoryCeiling.description: DURABLE: Kbytes of memory that the RMON event group may use.

cpqn52nnRmonMemoryUsed.name: cpqn52nnRmonMemoryUsed
cpqn52nnRmonMemoryUsed.description: Kbytes of memory used by RMON, rounded up.

cpqn52nnStatisticsMemoryUsed.name: cpqn52nnStatisticsMemoryUsed
cpqn52nnStatisticsMemoryUsed.description: Kbytes of memory that the RMON statistics group has used.

cpqn52nnHistoryMemoryUsed.name: cpqn52nnHistoryMemoryUsed
cpqn52nnHistoryMemoryUsed.description: Kbytes of memory that the RMON history group has used.

cpqn52nnAlarmMemoryUsed.name: cpqn52nnAlarmMemoryUsed
cpqn52nnAlarmMemoryUsed.description: Kbytes of memory that the RMON alarm group has used.

cpqn52nnEventMemoryUsed.name: cpqn52nnEventMemoryUsed
cpqn52nnEventMemoryUsed.description: Kbytes of memory that the RMON event group has used.

cpqn52nnMaxPktMemory.name: cpqn52nnMaxPktMemory
cpqn52nnMaxPktMemory.description: Kbytes of memory that can be used for Packet Memory.

cpqn52nnGlobalMemThreshTrapEnable.name: cpqn52nnGlobalMemThreshTrapEnable
cpqn52nnGlobalMemThreshTrapEnable.description: DURABLE: Enable Traps for all thresholding entries in the Global Memory group of objects. The default value is disabled.

cpqn52nnBcastMemThreshEnable.name: cpqn52nnBcastMemThreshEnable
cpqn52nnBcastMemThreshEnable.description: DURABLE: Enable thresholding for the Broadcast packet count. The default value is disabled.

cpqn52nnBcastPktCeiling.name: cpqn52nnBcastPktCeiling
cpqn52nnBcastPktCeiling.description: DURABLE: Value in 256 packet increments of the falling threshold of the maximum number of broadcast packets allowed in packet buffer memory.

cpqn52nnBcastHysteresisCtl.name: cpqn52nnBcastHysteresisCtl
cpqn52nnBcastHysteresisCtl.description: DURABLE: Number of packets that when added to the Bcast packet ceiling produces the Rising Threshold value of the maximum number of broadcast packets allowed in packet buffer memory.

cpqn52nnBcastPktCnt.name: cpqn52nnBcastPktCnt
cpqn52nnBcastPktCnt.description: Indicator of many broadcast packets are actually in packet buffer memory.

cpqn52nnBcastCongestionStatus.name: cpqn52nnBcastCongestionStatus
cpqn52nnBcastCongestionStatus.description: Indicator of broadcast packet congestion. When congested, the number of broadcast packets in packet buffer memory has exceeded the rising threshold, but has not gone below the falling threshold.

cpqn52nnPortMemThreshEntry.name: cpqn52nnPortMemThreshEntry
cpqn52nnPortMemThreshEntry.description: This table has one entry for each port. The index into the table is cpqn52nnPortThreshIfIndex.

cpqn52nnPortThreshIfIndex.name: cpqn52nnPortThreshIfIndex
cpqn52nnPortThreshIfIndex.description: The Interface Index as represented in MIB-II.

cpqn52nnPortTxPktThreshEnable.name: cpqn52nnPortTxPktThreshEnable
cpqn52nnPortTxPktThreshEnable.description: DURABLE: Enables or disabled transmit packet thresholding on a per port basis.

cpqn52nnPortTxPktCongestionStatus.name: cpqn52nnPortTxPktCongestionStatus
cpqn52nnPortTxPktCongestionStatus.description: Indicator of port transmit packet congestion. When congested, the number of transmit packets in packet buffer memory for the port has exceeded the rising threshold, but has not gone below the falling threshold.

cpqn52nnPortTxPktCnt.name: cpqn52nnPortTxPktCnt
cpqn52nnPortTxPktCnt.description: Indicator of how many transmit packets for the port are actually in packet buffer memory.

cpqn52nnPortTxPktCeiling.name: cpqn52nnPortTxPktCeiling
cpqn52nnPortTxPktCeiling.description: DURABLE: Value in 256 packet increments of the falling threshold of the maximum number of transmit packets allowed for the port in packet buffer memory.

cpqn52nnPortTxPktHysteresisCtl.name: cpqn52nnPortTxPktHysteresisCtl
cpqn52nnPortTxPktHysteresisCtl.description: DURABLE: Number of packets that when added to the port's transmit packet ceiling produces the Rising Threshold value of the maximum number of transmit packets allowed for the port in packet buffer memory.

cpqn52nnPortRxMemThreshEnable.name: cpqn52nnPortRxMemThreshEnable
cpqn52nnPortRxMemThreshEnable.description: DURABLE: Enables or disables receive memory thresholding on a per port basis.

cpqn52nnPortRxMemCongestionStatus.name: cpqn52nnPortRxMemCongestionStatus
cpqn52nnPortRxMemCongestionStatus.description: Indicator of port receive memory congestion. When congested, the amount of receive packet buffer memory used by the port has exceeded the rising threshold, but has not gone below the falling threshold.

cpqn52nnPortRxMemSectorCnt.name: cpqn52nnPortRxMemSectorCnt
cpqn52nnPortRxMemSectorCnt.description: Indicator of how amount Packet Receive memory, in 2Kbyte increments, is actually being used by the port.

cpqn52nnPortRxMemCeiling.name: cpqn52nnPortRxMemCeiling
cpqn52nnPortRxMemCeiling.description: DURABLE: Value in 32Kbyte increments of the falling threshold of the maximum receive packet memory allowed for the port in packet buffer memory.

cpqn52nnPortRxMemHysteresisCtl.name: cpqn52nnPortRxMemHysteresisCtl
cpqn52nnPortRxMemHysteresisCtl.description: DURABLE: Value in 2Kbyte increments that when added to the port's receive memory ceiling produces the Rising Threshold value of the maximum receive memory allowed for the port in packet buffer memory.

cpqn52nnPortCongestionTrapEnable.name: cpqn52nnPortCongestionTrapEnable
cpqn52nnPortCongestionTrapEnable.description: DURABLE: Enables or disabled traps due to congestion states for any Port.

cpqn52nnDramTable.name: cpqn52nnDramTable
cpqn52nnDramTable.description: This table defines the unit's Dram information.

cpqn52nnDramEntry.name: cpqn52nnDramEntry
cpqn52nnDramEntry.description: This table has one entry for each Dram component. The index into the table is cpqn52nnDramIndex.

cpqn52nnDramIndex.name: cpqn52nnDramIndex
cpqn52nnDramIndex.description: A simple index representing the area using the DRAM.

cpqn52nnDramSize.name: cpqn52nnDramSize
cpqn52nnDramSize.description: Size of DRAM being used, in KBytes.

cpqn52nnPortStatusTable.name: cpqn52nnPortStatusTable
cpqn52nnPortStatusTable.description: This table defines certain Port Level parameters for each port.

cpqn52nnPortStatusEntry.name: cpqn52nnPortStatusEntry
cpqn52nnPortStatusEntry.description: This table has one entry for each port. The index into the table is cpqn52nnPortStatusId.

cpqn52nnPortIfIndex.name: cpqn52nnPortIfIndex
cpqn52nnPortIfIndex.description: Switch interface number that corresponds to the interface in MIB-II.

cpqn52nnPortIfMauIndex.name: cpqn52nnPortIfMauIndex
cpqn52nnPortIfMauIndex.description: Uniquely identifies the port in the CPQN52nn unit for which additional info is being obtained.

cpqn52nnPortName.name: cpqn52nnPortName
cpqn52nnPortName.description: DURABLE: User defined name for port.

cpqn52nnPortType.name: cpqn52nnPortType
cpqn52nnPortType.description: This object identifies all possible port types. Note that unknown Port Types are represented by the value 1000.

cpqn52nnMdiMdixStatus.name: cpqn52nnMdiMdixStatus
cpqn52nnMdiMdixStatus.description: This object identifies all possible port types.

cpqn52nnMdiMdixEnable.name: cpqn52nnMdiMdixEnable
cpqn52nnMdiMdixEnable.description: This object identifies all possible port types.

cpqn52nnPortMonitorEntry.name: cpqn52nnPortMonitorEntry
cpqn52nnPortMonitorEntry.description: This table can be empty. Entries can be added as needed. The index into the table is cpqn52nnPortMonitorIndex.

cpqn52nnPortMonitorIndex.name: cpqn52nnPortMonitorIndex
cpqn52nnPortMonitorIndex.description: A simple index represnting the number of the entry being examined.

cpqn52nnPortMonitorRowStatus.name: cpqn52nnPortMonitorRowStatus
cpqn52nnPortMonitorRowStatus.description: DURABLE: The status of this row entry. Rows are added to this table using 'row sets'. When a row is added, this object must be set to row-valid(1). To delete a row from this table, set this object for the row to row-invalid(2). This object will always read as row-valid(1).

cpqn52nnPortMonitorIfIndex.name: cpqn52nnPortMonitorIfIndex
cpqn52nnPortMonitorIfIndex.description: DURABLE An index based on the interface index in MIB-II. This will represent the interface to be used to monitor the data of others as defined by cpqn52nnPortMonitoredIfMap.

cpqn52nnPortMonitoredIfMap.name: cpqn52nnPortMonitoredIfMap
cpqn52nnPortMonitoredIfMap.description: DURABLE: A bitmap indicating the ports whose data is being monitored. The bits used to represent the are the same as the IfIndex representation of the ports. e.g. port 25 --> 25th bit. An example is 0x00000003, indicates that ports 1 and 3 are being monitored. The port doing the monitoring is defined by cpqn52nnPortMonitorIfIndex for this row in the table.

cpqn52nnPortMonitoredDataType.name: cpqn52nnPortMonitoredDataType
cpqn52nnPortMonitoredDataType.description: DURABLE: The type of data to be monitored by the monitor port. Selecting TX or RX means that only the TX or RX data will be monitored by the monitor port.

cpqn52nnPortBondingTable.name: cpqn52nnPortBondingTable
cpqn52nnPortBondingTable.description: This table defines uplink bonding information.

cpqn52nnPortBondingEntry.name: cpqn52nnPortBondingEntry
cpqn52nnPortBondingEntry.description: The index into the table is cpqn52nnBondIndex. The table can be empty.

cpqn52nnBondIndex.name: cpqn52nnBondIndex
cpqn52nnBondIndex.description: A simple index representing the entry number.

cpqn52nnBondRowStatus.name: cpqn52nnBondRowStatus
cpqn52nnBondRowStatus.description: DURABLE: The status of this row entry. Rows are added to this table using 'row sets'. When a row is added, this object must be set to row-valid(1). To delete a row from this table, set this object for the row to row-invalid(2). This object will always read as row-valid(1).

cpqn52nnBondMap.name: cpqn52nnBondMap
cpqn52nnBondMap.description: DURABLE: A bitmap indicating the uplink ports that are bonded together. The bits used to represent the uplink ports are the same as the If Index representations of the ports. e.g. port 25 --> 25th bit. An example is 0x05000000, indicates that uplink ports 25 and 27 are bonded.

cpqn52nnIfStatusTable.name: cpqn52nnIfStatusTable
cpqn52nnIfStatusTable.description: This table defines certain switch interface level parameters for each interface.

cpqn52nnIfStatusEntry.name: cpqn52nnIfStatusEntry
cpqn52nnIfStatusEntry.description: This table has one entry for each switch interface. The index into the table is cpqn52nnIfStatusIfIndex.

cpqn52nnIfStatusIfIndex.name: cpqn52nnIfStatusIfIndex
cpqn52nnIfStatusIfIndex.description: The value of the instance of the ifIndex object, defined in MIB-II, for this switch interface.

cpqn52nnIfStatusIfType.name: cpqn52nnIfStatusIfType
cpqn52nnIfStatusIfType.description: The type of device used for this switch interface.

cpqn52nnIfStpStatus.name: cpqn52nnIfStpStatus
cpqn52nnIfStpStatus.description: When enabled(1), this interface will participate in Spanning Tree activities. When disabled(2), this interface will not participate in the Spanning Tree algorithm. Default is enabled(1). DURABLE.

cpqn52nnIfResetStatus.name: cpqn52nnIfResetStatus
cpqn52nnIfResetStatus.description: This object will allow the user to physically reset an interface on the CPQN52nn. The advantage over a general reset is that the other interfaces are left unaffected in their operation. The agent will always return interface-not-resetting(1) when the object is read.

cpqn52nnIfLearningStatus.name: cpqn52nnIfLearningStatus
cpqn52nnIfLearningStatus.description: When enabled(1), this interface can enter the learning state. When disabled(2), this interface is not allowed to enter the learning state. When disabled(2), Spanning Tree must be set to disabled. Default is enabled(1). DURABLE.

cpqn52nnIfAgingStatus.name: cpqn52nnIfAgingStatus
cpqn52nnIfAgingStatus.description: When enabled(1), this interface ages learned entries in the Address Filter/Forward table. When disabled(2), this interface does not age entries in the address table. Default is enabled(1). DURABLE.

cpqn52nnIfAgingTime.name: cpqn52nnIfAgingTime
cpqn52nnIfAgingTime.description: The timeout period in seconds for aging out dynamically learned forwarding information on the switch interface. DURABLE

cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeSrcStatus.name: cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeSrcStatus
cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeSrcStatus.description: The switch mode for this interface when it is the Source in a switch transfer.

cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeDestStatus.name: cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeDestStatus
cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeDestStatus.description: The switch mode for this interface when it is the Destination in a switch transfer.

cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeSrc.name: cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeSrc
cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeSrc.description: DURABLE: The switch mode for this interface when it is the Source in a switch transfer. The default case is store-and-forward(1).

cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeDest.name: cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeDest
cpqn52nnIfSwitchModeDest.description: DURABLE: The switch mode for this interface when it is the Destination in a switch transfer. The default case is store-and-forward(1).

cpqn52nnIfArbPriority.name: cpqn52nnIfArbPriority
cpqn52nnIfArbPriority.description: DURABLE: The priority mechanism used for arbitration. The possible arbitration states and values are as follows: VALUE ARBITRATION ----- ----------- 0 First-Come-First-Served all port same Round Robin (Fair) all ports varied Round Robin (Weighted) The final case implies that not all ports have the same priority in which case a weighted Round Robin method of arbitration would be used. The default case has all ports with a value of 0 (First-Come-First-Served).

cpqn52nnQuadIfTable.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfTable
cpqn52nnQuadIfTable.description: This table provides information, on a per port basis, for the Quad Cascade devices.

cpqn52nnQuadIfEntry.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfEntry
cpqn52nnQuadIfEntry.description: This table has one entry for each Port. The indices into the table are cpqn52nnQuadIfIndex.

cpqn52nnQuadIfIndex.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfIndex
cpqn52nnQuadIfIndex.description: An index representing the interface as in MIN-II.

cpqn52nnQuadIfAlignFcsErrors.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfAlignFcsErrors
cpqn52nnQuadIfAlignFcsErrors.description: Shows the number of packets received between 64 and 1518 bytes in length, but were not an integral number of bytes in length, or had a bad Frame Check Sequence.

cpqn52nnQuadIfTxRunts.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfTxRunts
cpqn52nnQuadIfTxRunts.description: Shows the number of packets transmitted that were less than 64 bytes in length.

cpqn52nnQuadIfRxRunts.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfRxRunts
cpqn52nnQuadIfRxRunts.description: Shows the number of packets received that were less than 64 bytes long that were an integral number of bytes long.

cpqn52nnQuadIfTotalCollisions.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfTotalCollisions
cpqn52nnQuadIfTotalCollisions.description: Shows the number of collision packets, single and multiple.

cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgTable.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgTable
cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgTable.description: This table provides information, on a per port basis, for the Quad Cascade devices.

cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgEntry.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgEntry
cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgEntry.description: This table has one entry for each Port. The index into the table is cpqn52nnQuadIfIndex.

cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgIndex.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgIndex
cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgIndex.description: An index representing the interface as in MIN-II.

cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgLinkForce.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgLinkForce
cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgLinkForce.description: DURABLE: When enabled, this object allows the port to transmit even if link integrity fails.

cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgLinkPolarityCorrect.name: cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgLinkPolarityCorrect
cpqn52nnQuadIfCfgLinkPolarityCorrect.description: DURABLE: When enabled, this allows the port to correct for inverted polarity on the twisted pair interface, if an inverted polarity condition exists on that port.

cpqn52nnTlanIfTable.name: cpqn52nnTlanIfTable
cpqn52nnTlanIfTable.description: This table provides information, on a per port basis, for the Tlan devices.

cpqn52nnTlanIfEntry.name: cpqn52nnTlanIfEntry
cpqn52nnTlanIfEntry.description: This table has one entry for each Port. The index into the table is cpqn52nnTlanIfIndex.

cpqn52nnTlanIfIndex.name: cpqn52nnTlanIfIndex
cpqn52nnTlanIfIndex.description: A simple index representing the Port in the table representing the IfIndex in MIB-II.

cpqn52nnTlanIfTxGoodFrms.name: cpqn52nnTlanIfTxGoodFrms
cpqn52nnTlanIfTxGoodFrms.description: Shows the number of packets transmitted that were good (no errors).

cpqn52nnTlanIfRxUndersizeFrms.name: cpqn52nnTlanIfRxUndersizeFrms
cpqn52nnTlanIfRxUndersizeFrms.description: Shows the number of packets that were

cpqn52nnTlanIfRxOverruns.name: cpqn52nnTlanIfRxOverruns
cpqn52nnTlanIfRxOverruns.description: Shows the number of packets received that were

cpqn52nnTlanIfRxAlignSymbolErrs.name: cpqn52nnTlanIfRxAlignSymbolErrs
cpqn52nnTlanIfRxAlignSymbolErrs.description: Shows the number of packets received that had either Alignment errors or Symbol errors.

cpqn52nnHashStaticNum.name: cpqn52nnHashStaticNum
cpqn52nnHashStaticNum.description: A count of static entries in this switch interface's Address Forwarding/Filtering mechanism.

cpqn52nnHashDynamicNum.name: cpqn52nnHashDynamicNum
cpqn52nnHashDynamicNum.description: A count of dynamic entries in this switch interface's Address Forwarding/Filtering mechanism.

cpqn52nnHashChainNum.name: cpqn52nnHashChainNum
cpqn52nnHashChainNum.description: A count of indices in the Address Filter/Forward mechanism's hash table which have more than one MAC Address entry.

cpqn52nnHashChainLength.name: cpqn52nnHashChainLength
cpqn52nnHashChainLength.description: A count of the number of MAC Address entries in the longest chain in the Address Filter/Forward mechanism's hash table.

cpqn52nnDropsWholeMemoryCtr.name: cpqn52nnDropsWholeMemoryCtr
cpqn52nnDropsWholeMemoryCtr.description: Counter to indicate the total number of packets dropped due to memory overflow. This is exclusive of the other counters in this section.

cpqn52nnDropsBcastMemoryCtr.name: cpqn52nnDropsBcastMemoryCtr
cpqn52nnDropsBcastMemoryCtr.description: Counter to indicate the total number of packets dropped due to memory overflow in the area handling Broadcast packets only. This is exclusive of the other counters in this section.

cpqn52nnDropsIfMemoryCtr.name: cpqn52nnDropsIfMemoryCtr
cpqn52nnDropsIfMemoryCtr.description: Counter to indicate the total number of packets dropped due to memory overflow in the area handling interface TX/RX packets only. This is exclusive of the other counters in this section.

cpqn52nnBusMonTable.name: cpqn52nnBusMonTable
cpqn52nnBusMonTable.description: This table defines the unit's utilization information.

cpqn52nnBusMonEntry.name: cpqn52nnBusMonEntry
cpqn52nnBusMonEntry.description: This table has one entry for each bus component. The index into the table is cpqn52nnBusMonIndex.

cpqn52nnBusMonIndex.name: cpqn52nnBusMonIndex
cpqn52nnBusMonIndex.description: A simple index representing the entry in the table.

cpqn52nnBusMonRowStatus.name: cpqn52nnBusMonRowStatus
cpqn52nnBusMonRowStatus.description: DURABLE: The status of this alarm entry.

cpqn52nnBusMonBusType.name: cpqn52nnBusMonBusType
cpqn52nnBusMonBusType.description: DURABLE: The type of bus to be monitored.

cpqn52nnBusMonDataType.name: cpqn52nnBusMonDataType
cpqn52nnBusMonDataType.description: DURABLE: The type of data to be monitored.

cpqn52nnBusMonPktType.name: cpqn52nnBusMonPktType
cpqn52nnBusMonPktType.description: DURABLE: The type of data to be monitored.

cpqn52nnBusMonSwitchModeType.name: cpqn52nnBusMonSwitchModeType
cpqn52nnBusMonSwitchModeType.description: DURABLE: The type of packets monitored for data.

cpqn52nnBusMonCurrentUtilization.name: cpqn52nnBusMonCurrentUtilization
cpqn52nnBusMonCurrentUtilization.description: Utilization of the selected port calculated as a percentage of the total bandwidth available for the bus.

cpqn52nnBusMonPeakUtilization.name: cpqn52nnBusMonPeakUtilization
cpqn52nnBusMonPeakUtilization.description: Utilization of the selected port calculated as a percentage of the total bandwidth available for the bus.

cpqn52nnBusMonRisingThreshold.name: cpqn52nnBusMonRisingThreshold
cpqn52nnBusMonRisingThreshold.description: DURABLE: If this threshold is exceeded, then the action listed in ThresholdAction will take place. The value is a % utilzation.

cpqn52nnBusMonFallingThreshold.name: cpqn52nnBusMonFallingThreshold
cpqn52nnBusMonFallingThreshold.description: DURABLE: If this threshold is exceeded, then the action listed in ThresholdAction will take place. The value is a % utilzation.

cpqn52nnBusMonAction.name: cpqn52nnBusMonAction
cpqn52nnBusMonAction.description: DURABLE: If this threshold is exceeded, then the action listed in ThresholdAction will take place. The value is an absolute number in bytes/sec.

cpqn52nnBusMonTrapEnable.name: cpqn52nnBusMonTrapEnable
cpqn52nnBusMonTrapEnable.description: DURABLE: Enable Trap Generation if threshold is exceeded.

cpqn52nnPowerSupplyStatusTrap.name: cpqn52nnPowerSupplyStatusTrap
cpqn52nnPowerSupplyStatusTrap.description: A cpqn52nnPowerSupplyStatus Trap is sent whenever a power supply changes state from voltage-ok to voltage-not-ok or vice versa.

cpqn52nnUplinkInsertedTrap.name: cpqn52nnUplinkInsertedTrap
cpqn52nnUplinkInsertedTrap.description: The cpqn52nnMepInserted trap is sent whenever a MEP, that represents a physical interface, is added.

cpqn52nnUplinkRemovedTrap.name: cpqn52nnUplinkRemovedTrap
cpqn52nnUplinkRemovedTrap.description: The cpqn52nnMepRemoved trap is sent whenever a MEP, that represents a physical interface, is removed.

cpqn52nnBusMonRisingThresholdTrap.name: cpqn52nnBusMonRisingThresholdTrap
cpqn52nnBusMonRisingThresholdTrap.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an alarm entry crosses its rising threshold and generates an event that is configured for sending SNMP traps.

cpqn52nnBusMonFallingThresholdTrap.name: cpqn52nnBusMonFallingThresholdTrap
cpqn52nnBusMonFallingThresholdTrap.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an alarm entry crosses its falling threshold and generates an event that is configured for sending SNMP traps.

cpqb52nnGlobalBcastMemCongestionTrap.name: cpqb52nnGlobalBcastMemCongestionTrap
cpqb52nnGlobalBcastMemCongestionTrap.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an alarm entry crosses its rising or falling threshold and generates an event that is configured for sending SNMP traps.

cpqb52nnPortTxPktCongestionTrap.name: cpqb52nnPortTxPktCongestionTrap
cpqb52nnPortTxPktCongestionTrap.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an alarm entry crosses its rising or falling threshold and generates an event that is configured for sending SNMP traps.

cpqb52nnPortRxMemCongestionTrap.name: cpqb52nnPortRxMemCongestionTrap
cpqb52nnPortRxMemCongestionTrap.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an alarm entry crosses its rising or falling threshold and generates an event that is configured for sending SNMP traps.
